      <title>Time to Change Lebanese Law That Offers Rapists Marriage to Survivors</title>
      <category domain="https://www.newsdeeply.com/womenandgirls/gender-based-violence/">Gender-Based Violence</category>
      <pubDate>Thu, 11 May 2017 12:47:46 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>Myriam Sfeir</author>
      <link>https://www.newsdeeply.com/womenandgirls/community/2017/05/11/time-to-change-lebanese-law-that-offers-rapists-marriage</link>
      <guid>https://www.newsdeeply.com/womenandgirls/community/2017/05/11/time-to-change-lebanese-law-that-offers-rapists-marriage</guid>
      <description>Lebanon’s government has the opportunity to repeal a law allowing rapists to escape punishment by marrying the women they’ve abused. Myriam Sfeir of the Institute for Women’s Studies in the Arab World says it’s time the country’s politicians stood up for women’s rights.</description>
